#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.15"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.15:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.15:0.2"
msgid "2. Nāthavagga"
msgstr "2. A Protector"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.15:0.3"
msgid "15. Appamādasutta"
msgstr "15. Diligence"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Yāvatā, bhikkhave, sattā apadā vā dvipadā vā catuppadā vā bahuppadā vā "
"rūpino vā arūpino vā saññino vā asaññino vā nevasaññināsaññino vā, tathāgato "
"tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho;"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, "
"is said to be the best of all sentient beings—be they footless, with two "
"feet, four feet, or many feet; with form or formless; with perception or "
"without perception or with neither perception nor non-perception."

#. VAR: Appamādo tesaṃ → tesaṃ dhammānaṃ (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an10.15:1.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā "
"appamādasamosaraṇā. Appamādo tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati. (1)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at "
"diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: jaṅgalānaṃ → jaṅgamānaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an10.15:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici jaṅgalānaṃ pāṇānaṃ padajātāni, sabbāni "
"tāni hatthipade samodhānaṃ gacchanti, hatthipadaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, "
"yadidaṃ mahantattena;"
msgstr ""
"The footprints of all creatures that walk can fit inside an elephant’s "
"footprint, so an elephant’s footprint is said to be the biggest of them all."

#. VAR: Appamādo tesaṃ → tesaṃ dhammānaṃ (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an10.15:2.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā "
"appamādasamosaraṇā. Appamādo tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati. (2)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at "
"diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:3.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, kūṭāgārassa yā kāci gopānasiyo sabbā tā kūṭaṅgamā "
"kūṭaninnā kūṭasamosaraṇā, kūṭo tāsaṃ aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"The rafters of a bungalow all lean to the peak, slope to the peak, and meet "
"at the peak, so the peak is said to be the topmost of them all."

msgctxt "an10.15:3.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā "
"appamādasamosaraṇā. Appamādo tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati. (3)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at "
"diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them."

# BB has Black orris, which appears to be incorrect. According to Dhammika, it is spikenard.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.22"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci mūlagandhā, kāḷānusāriyaṃ tesaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr "Of all kinds of fragrant root, spikenard is said to be the best."

msgctxt "an10.15:4.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave … pe …. (4)"
msgstr "In the same way …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:5.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci sāragandhā, lohitacandanaṃ tesaṃ "
"aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"Of all kinds of fragrant heartwood, red sandalwood is said to be the best."

msgctxt "an10.15:5.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave … pe …. (5)"
msgstr "In the same way …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:6.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci pupphagandhā, vassikaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr "Of all kinds of fragrant flower, jasmine is said to be the best."

msgctxt "an10.15:6.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave … pe …. (6)"
msgstr "In the same way …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: khuddarājāno → kuḍḍarājāno (bj, s3, pts1) | kuḍḍarājā (s1, s2) | kūṭarājāno (mr)
msgctxt "an10.15:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, ye keci khuddarājāno, sabbe te rañño cakkavattissa "
"anuyantā bhavanti, rājā tesaṃ cakkavattī aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"All lesser kings are vassals of a wheel-turning monarch, so the wheel-"
"turning monarch is said to be the foremost of them all."

msgctxt "an10.15:7.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave … pe …. (7)"
msgstr "In the same way …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:8.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yā kāci tārakarūpānaṃ pabhā, sabbā tā candappabhāya "
"kalaṃ nāgghanti soḷasiṃ, candappabhā tāsaṃ aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"The radiance of all the stars is not worth a sixteenth part of the moon’s "
"radiance, so the moon’s radiance is said to be the best of them all."

msgctxt "an10.15:8.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave … pe …. (8)"
msgstr "In the same way …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
#. VAR: abbhussakkamāno → abbhussukkamāno (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "an10.15:9.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, saradasamaye viddhe vigatavalāhake deve ādicco nabhaṃ "
"abbhussakkamāno sabbaṃ ākāsagataṃ tamagataṃ abhivihacca bhāsate ca tapate ca "
"virocati ca;"
msgstr ""
"After the rainy season the sky is clear and cloudless. And when the sun "
"rises, it dispels all the darkness from the sky as it shines and glows and "
"radiates."

msgctxt "an10.15:9.2"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave … pe …. (9)"
msgstr "In the same way …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an10.15:10.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yā kāci mahānadiyo, seyyathidaṃ—gaṅgā, yamunā, "
"aciravatī, sarabhū, mahī, sabbā tā samuddaṅgamā samuddaninnā samuddapoṇā "
"samuddapabbhārā, mahāsamuddo tāsaṃ aggamakkhāyati;"
msgstr ""
"All the great rivers—that is, the Ganges, Yamunā, Aciravatī, Sarabhū, and "
"Mahī—flow, slant, slope, and incline towards the ocean, and the ocean is "
"said to be the greatest of them."

msgctxt "an10.15:10.2"
msgid ""
"evamevaṃ kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā "
"appamādasamosaraṇā. Appamādo tesaṃ aggamakkhāyatī”ti. (10)"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at "
"diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.15:10.3"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
